00613  *
00614  * These functions will fill in RNA pointers, this can be done in three ways:
00615  * - a pointer Main is created by just passing the data pointer
00616  * - a pointer to a datablock can be created with the type and id data pointer
00617  * - a pointer to data contained in a datablock can be created with the id type
00618  *   and id data pointer, and the data type and pointer to the struct itself.
00619  *
00620  * There is also a way to get a pointer with the information about all structs.
00621  */
